{"title_page": "1968 Cincinnati Bearcats football team", "text_new": "{{short description|American college football season}}\n{{Infobox NCAA team season\n| mode = football\n| year = 1968\n| team = Cincinnati Bearcats\n| conference = Missouri Valley Conference\n| short_conf = MVC\n| division = \n| record = 5\u20134\u20131\n| conf_record = 2\u20132\u20130\n| head_coach = [[Homer Rice]]\n| hc_year = 2nd\n| off_scheme = \n| def_scheme = \n| captain = [[Greg Cook]], Milt Balkum\n| stadium = [[Nippert Stadium]]\n| champion = \n}}\n{{1968 Missouri Valley Conference football standings}}\nThe '''1968 Cincinnati Bearcats football team''' represented [[University of Cincinnati]] during the [[1968 NCAA University Division football season]]. The Bearcats, led by head coach [[Homer Rice]], participated in the [[Missouri Valley Conference]] (MVC) and played their home games at [[Nippert Stadium]].\n\n==Schedule==\n{{CFB schedule\n| rankyear = 1968\n\n|{{CFB schedule entry\n| date = September 21\n| w/l = t\n| nonconf = y\n| away = y\n| opponent = [[1968 Texas Tech Red Raiders football team|Texas Tech]]\n| site_stadium = [[Clifford B. and Audrey Jones Stadium]]\n| site_cityst = [[Lubbock, Texas|Lubbock, TX]]\n| score = 10\u201310\n}}\n|{{CFB schedule entry\n| date = September 28\n| w/l = w\n| nonconf = y\n| opponent = {{cfb link|year=1968|team=Xavier Musketeers|title=Xavier}}\n| site_stadium = [[Nippert Stadium]]\n| site_cityst = [[Cincinnati|Cincinnati, OH]]\n| gamename = [[Cincinnati\u2013Xavier rivalry#Football|Rivalry]]\n| score = 17\u201314\n}}\n|{{CFB schedule entry\n| date = October 4\n| w/l = l\n| nonconf = y\n| away = y\n| opponent = [[1968 Houston Cougars football team|Houston]]\n| opprank = 12\n| site_stadium = [[Astrodome]]\n| site_cityst = [[Houston|Houston, TX]]\n| score = 33\u201371\n}}\n|{{CFB schedule entry\n| date = October 12\n| w/l = w\n| nonconf = y\n| opponent = [[1968 Tampa Spartans football team|Tampa]]\n| site_stadium = Nippert Stadium\n| site_cityst = Cinci